1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Bc5 3. Bc4 {A reasonable response. White delays f4.} 3... Nf6
4. d3 {Preparing to capture on f4 with the Bishop if Black should choose to
take the pawn.} 4... O-O 5. f4 d6 6. f5 {White's idea here is to gain space on
the kingside and attack with pawns. In this game, the plan works to perfection.
} (6. Nf3 Nc6 7. f5 {comes to the same thing.}) 6... Nc6 7. Nf3 Bd7 8. Na4 $1 {
Getting rid of Black's darksquare Bishop, his most active piece.} 8... Bb6 9.
Nxb6 axb6 10. O-O Ne7 11. Bg5 Ne8 12. Qe1 h6 13. Bh4 Bc6 14. Qg3 Qd7 $2 (14...
Kh8 {or 14...Kh7 was forced.}) 15. f6 $1 {Ow!} 15... Ng6 16. fxg7 {
Here we can see that the game was a blitz game.} (16. Qxg6 $1 {
wins immediately because of some simple but pretty tactics:} 16... d5 17. exd5
$1 fxg6 18. dxc6+ Qf7 19. cxb7 $18) 16... Nxg7 17. Bf6 (17. Qxg6 d5 18. Qxh6
dxc4 19. Bf6 $1 Qg4 20. Ng5 $1 {and White mates.}) 17... Nh5 $4 18. Qxg6+ 1-0

