1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 Bc5 4. fxe5 Bd4 {Well, this is certainly original!
But Black will regret the time lost with this piece.} (4... Bxg1 5. Rxg1 Qh4+
6. g3 Qxh2 7. Rg2 $1 Qh3 8. Nd5 $1 Kd8 9. d4 $18 {
White has a commanding center.}) 5. Nf3 Bxe5 6. d4 Bd6 7. Bc4 Nge7 {This move i
s almost always a mistake in these lines. White gets in a quick Ng5 and Black
is toast.} 8. Ng5 $1 Rf8 (8... O-O 9. Qh5 $1 {and Black loses on h7 or f7, e.g.
} 9... h6 10. Nxf7 Qe8 11. Nxh6+ Kh7 12. Nf7+ Kg8 13. Qh8#) 9. O-O f6 10. Nxh7
b6 11. Nxf8 Kxf8 12. Qh5 1-0

