1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 d6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bb5 $1 {
It is useful to prevent this Knight from coming to d4.} 5... Bg4 6. d3 Be7 7.
fxe5 dxe5 8. O-O (8. Bxc6+ {is also good right away.}) 8... O-O 9. Bxc6 {
It is important to make this capture before the Knight can jump to d4.} 9...
bxc6 10. Qe1 Bc5+ 11. Kh1 {Black's pawn structure is terrible here, and his
Bishop pair has no concrete targets. Additionally, White has good chances to
launch a swift attack along the open f-file.} 11... Bxf3 12. Rxf3 h6 13. Qh4
Be7 14. Bxh6 $1 gxh6 (14... Nh7 15. Qg3 $1 Bg5 16. Bxg5 Nxg5 17. Rf5 f6 18.
Raf1 $18) 15. Qxh6 Nh7 (15... Ng4 16. Rg3 $18) 16. Rh3 {Black resigns} 1-0

