{I have to wonder whether perhaps the names were reversed on this game and
Alekhine was playing White!} 1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 exf4 4. Nf3 g5 5. d4 g4
6. Bc4 gxf3 7. Bxf4 {Whoa!!} 7... fxg2 8. Bxf7+ Kxf7 9. Qh5+ Kg7 10. Rg1 {
White is already much better, perhaps winning!} 10... Nge7 (10... Bb4 11. Rxg2+
Kf8 12. Bh6+ Nxh6 13. Qxh6+ Ke8 14. Qh5+ Kf8 15. Rf2+ Kg7 16. Qg4+ Kh6 17. Rf5
{and White mates.}) 11. Bh6+ $1 Kg8 12. Rxg2+ 1-0

