1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 exf4 4. Nf3 g5 5. d4 (5. Bc4 g4 6. O-O gxf3 7. Qxf3
Ne5 8. Qxf4 f6 9. Be2 $1 {and White has good compensation for his material.})
5... g4 {Okay, so you want to play rough ...} 6. Bc4 $5 gxf3 7. O-O {This is a 
classic gambit line, similar to the Muzio Gambit. It is terribly hard to play
for Black since White mounts very serious threats very quickly.} 7... d5 8.
exd5 Bg4 9. Qd2 Na5 10. Bb5+ c6 11. Qxf4 $1 Qd7 12. Qe5+ $1 Ne7 13. Ne4 $1
O-O-O 14. Bf4 $1 1-0

