1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 exf4 4. Nf3 d6 5. d4 g5 {
Here we get to see how a GM handles this line.} 6. d5 $1 Ne5 7. Bb5+ $1 Bd7 8.
Bxd7+ $1 Nxd7 9. h4 {I prefer 9.Qd4, but Hector's move is very good as well.}
9... g4 10. Nd4 {Now Black's pawns look like sitting ducks.} 10... h5 (10...
Bg7 11. Bxf4 $14) (10... Bh6 11. Qxg4 $16) 11. Bxf4 {This pawn structure is
interesting. Black's pawn on f7 is a long-term target, and White has good play
on the f-file in general.} 11... Bh6 12. Bxh6 Nxh6 13. Qd2 Qe7 14. O-O-O O-O-O
$2 {Black misses a tactical trick.} 15. Ncb5 $1 (15. Ncb5 a6 (15... Qxe4 16.
Qa5 Nb6 (16... b6 17. Qa6+ Kb8 18. Qxa7+ Kc8 19. Qxc7#) 17. Nxa7+ Kd7 (17...
Kb8 18. Ndc6+ bxc6 19. Qa6 $18 {and White mates shortly.}) 18. Qb5+ Ke7 19.
Rhe1 $18) (15... Kb8 16. Qa5 {and Black falls apart on c7 and a7.}) 16. Na7+
Kb8 17. Nac6+ bxc6 18. Nxc6+ $18) 1-0

