1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 Bc5 4. fxe5 Bxg1 5. exf6 (5. Rxg1 {
would be just fine here, e.g.} 5... Ng8 6. Qg4 Kf8 7. Qf4 $18 {
and White is a pawn ahead with a dominating center.}) 5... Qxf6 $4 (5... Bd4
$16 {
still leaves White much better, but at least Black would not be a piece down.})
6. Rxg1 Qh4+ 7. g3 Qxh2 8. Rg2 $1 {Simple chess. White keeps both the Rook and
the g-pawn guarded and gains time kicking Black's Queen away.} 8... Qh6 9. Nd5
{There are many good moves to choose from here.} (9. d4) (9. Qf3) 9... O-O 10.
Nxc7 (10. d4 Qc6 $4 (10... Qd6 11. Bf4 $18) 11. Ne7+) 10... Qc6 11. Nxa8 b6 12.
d3 1-0

