1. Nc3 {Patience! It will turn into a Vienna in a moment.} 1... e5 2. e4 Nf6 3.
f4 d6 4. Nf3 Bg4 5. Bc4 $6 {
Not the most precise move. White should immediately "biff" the Bishop.} (5. h3
{is best right away. But this game does feature some interesting tactics, so
it is worth playing over even though White's play is very careless.}) 5... Nc6
6. fxe5 $2 {Black's Bishop on f8 was in prison. Why let it out for free?} (6.
d3 {is about equal.}) 6... dxe5 (6... Nxe5 {would force} 7. Be2 {
when White has only a slilght advantage.}) 7. O-O $4 {
Incredibly careless for a player rated nearly 1700.} (7. d3 {
is best, with dead equality.}) 7... Nd4 $4 {Black returns the favor.} 8. Bxf7+
$1 {White redeems himself with a nice combination.} 8... Kxf7 9. Nxe5+ Kg8 10.
Nxg4 Nxg4 11. Qxg4 Nxc2 $4 {
Black incorrectly assumes that the tactics are over.} 12. Qe6# 1-0

