1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 exf4 4. e5 Qe7 $2 {
There are several other examples of this common error in this file.} 5. Qe2 Ng8
6. Nf3 d6 7. Nd5 $1 {White plays to push Black's Queen off of the e-file so
that he will have a discovered check.} 7... Qd8 8. exd6+ Be6 9. Nxc7+ Kd7 10.
Ne5+ Kc8 (10... Kxd6 11. Nxe6 Kxe6 (11... fxe6 12. Nf7+ $18 {
This fork wins Black's Queen.}) 12. Nc6+ {
The discovered check wins Black's Queen.}) 11. Nxe6 fxe6 12. Qc4+ Nc6 13. Qxc6+
$3 bxc6 14. Ba6+ Kb8 15. Nxc6# {This game was reproduced approximately 100
years later (!) in Tim McGrew - Scott Noldy, a casual lunchtime game in
highschool that ended Scott's willingness to play chess with me.} 1-0

