1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 exf4 4. e5 Qe7 5. Qe2 $1 Ng8 6. d4 (6. Nf3 $1 {
is more accurate right away, stopping any chance for Black to give a Queen
check on h4.}) 6... Nc6 7. Nf3 g5 8. Nd5 $1 Qd8 {
Now we get to see something very nice.} 9. Nf6+ $1 Ke7 (9... Nxf6 10. exf6+ Be7
{and White can take the Bishop immediately or simply play} 11. c3 $18) 10. d5 (
10. Nxg5 {is also winning here, e.g.} 10... Nxd4 11. Qc4 $1 $18) 10... Nb8 11.
d6+ $1 cxd6 12. Nd5+ $1 Ke6 13. exd6+ {
Just one of many ways to win at this point.} (13. Nd4+ $1 Kxd5 14. Qb5+ $1 Kxd4
15. c3+ Ke4 16. Bd3#) 13... Kxd6 (13... Kf5 14. Qd3+ Ke6 15. Qe4+ Kxd6 16. Qe5+
Kc6 17. Nd4+ Kc5 18. b4#) 14. Qe5+ Kc6 15. Nd4+ Kc5 16. b4# 1-0

