1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 exf4 4. e5 Qe7 $2 {
This looks clever, but Black's Queen is exposed on this square.} 5. Qe2 Ng8 6.
Nf3 c6 {This has the advantage of keeping a White Knight out of d5, but Black
is still very far behind in development and White's moves are very natural.} 7.
Ne4 $1 {Threatening to jump into the hole at d6.} 7... d5 $2 {
Black has forgotten something important.} 8. exd6 $1 Qe6 9. Nfg5 $1 {
Driving the Queen off of the e-file.} 9... Qg4 10. Nf6+ $1 {
Not just winning the Queen ...} (10. Nf6+ Kd8 11. Nxf7#) 1-0

