1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 exf4 4. e5 Ng8 5. Nf3 Be7 {
Black would like to get in a check at h4, disorienting White.} 6. Bc4 $1 {
This is a simple way to meet the threat. White clears the f1 square for his
King.} 6... Bh4+ 7. Kf1 {The White King is reasonably comfortable here.} 7...
Nc6 8. d4 g5 $2 {This is very careless.} 9. Nxh4 $1 {
Of course! White shatters the Black kingside pawns.} 9... gxh4 10. Qh5 $1 {
Now Black collapses quickly.} 10... Qe7 11. Nd5 $1 (11. Nd5 Qd8 12. Nxc7+ Qxc7
13. Qxf7+ Kd8 14. Qf8#) 1-0

