8. d4 (8. g4 $1 {
wins a piece, though at first it looks like Black can wriggle out with} 8... c6
{But then White has} 9. Nf6+ $1 Nxf6 10. exf6+ $18 {
and Black must lose a piece on e7.}) 8... c6 9. Bg5 $5 (9. Nc3 $1 {
is simple and strong.}) 9... f6 $4 {
Black has forgotten that White has a Queen on the e-file.} 10. exf6+ Kf7 11.
Ne5+ Ke6 12. Nxc6+ {Simplest. Take the money and run!} 12... Kxd5 13. Nxd8 Kd6
14. Qe5# 1-0

