1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 exf4 4. e5 Ng8 5. Nf3 d6 6. Qe2 $5 {Up until now I
have thought that 6.d4 was best, but this game makes me want to reconsider.}
6... Qe7 $4 {Plausible -- and fatal.} (6... d5 {A difficult move to find after
one has played ...d6. Fritz at first gives this as Black's best, but gradually
it appears that Black has lost too much time.} 7. d4 g5 {
anything else gives White at least a slight edge.} 8. e6 $5 {This pawn sacrific
e clears the e5 square, after which Black must immediately give back one and
probably both of the pawns.} (8. h4 $5 {
This is a radical approach to the kingside situation.} 8... g4 9. Ng1 (9. Ng5 {
This looks too optimistic.} 9... h6 10. Nxf7 Kxf7 11. Bxf4 $19 {
I suspect Black can hold here.}) 9... Nc6 10. Qf2 g3 11. Qxf4 Bh6 12. Qxg3 Nxd4
13. Bd3 $14) (8. Qf2 {This is insufficiently challenging to Black's setup.}
8... Bg7 9. Bd3 Nc6 10. O-O Bg4 $17) 8... Bxe6 (8... fxe6 9. Qe5 Qf6 10. Qxg5
Bh6 11. Qh5+ Kf8 12. Bd3 c5 13. Nb5 Nc6 14. dxc5 Qf7 15. Qxf7+ Kxf7 16. Nd6+
$14) 9. Qe5 Nf6 (9... Qf6 10. Qxf6 Nxf6 11. Nxg5 f3 12. Nxf3 Bb4 13. Bd2 {
Fritz thinks White's edge is nominal, and while this is perhaps true I think
I'd be decidedly more comfortable with White here.}) 10. Nxg5 Bd6 11. Nxe6 fxe6
12. Qxe6+ Qe7 13. Qxe7+ Kxe7 14. Nb5 Nc6 15. c3 Rae8 16. Be2 f3 17. Bxf3 a6 18.
Nxd6 Kxd6+ 19. Kd1 $16) (6... dxe5 {This is probably Black's best hope.} 7. d4
(7. Qxe5+ Be6 (7... Qe7 8. d4 Qxe5+ 9. Nxe5 g5 10. g3 fxg3 11. hxg3 $16 f6 12.
Ng6 $18) 8. Nb5 Na6 9. Nbd4 Qd5 10. Bb5+ c6 11. Bxa6 bxa6 12. Qxf4 $14) 7...
Bd6 (7... Be6 8. Qxe5 Nd7 (8... Nc6 9. Bb5 Nge7 10. Bxf4 Rc8 11. d5 $16)) (7...
f6 8. dxe5 fxe5 9. Bxf4 $16) 8. Bxf4 $14) (6... Be7 7. d4 dxe5 8. Qxe5 Nd7 9.
Qxf4 $14) (6... Be6 7. Qb5+ (7. d4 dxe5 8. Qxe5 Nd7 9. Qxf4 Ngf6 10. Ng5 $14)
7... Nd7 8. exd6 Bxd6 9. Qxb7 $14) 7. Nd5 $1 {
Black has walked into one of the worst possible lines by transposition.} 7...
Qd7 8. Nxc7+ Kd8 (8... Qxc7 9. exd6+ $18) 9. Nxa8 Nc6 10. d4 dxe5 11. dxe5 f6
12. Bxf4 Qe7 13. O-O-O+ Ke8 14. e6 1-0

