1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 exf4 4. e5 Ng8 5. Nf3 f6 6. d4 Bb4 7. Bxf4 d6 8. exd6
Bxd6 9. Qd2 Bg4 10. O-O-O Ne7 11. Bc4 Nbc6 12. Rhe1 Qd7 13. h3 {
This is the simplest way to get a clear edge.} (13. Bxd6 cxd6 14. d5 {
Now it seems that the Knight cannot move because of Bb5 pinning and winning
the Queen. But this is not quite true: there is one tactical possibility.}
14... Nb4 15. a3 (15. Bb5 $2 Nxa2+ $1 16. Nxa2 Qxb5 $17) 15... Bxf3 16. gxf3
Rc8 17. axb4 Rxc4 18. Rxe7+ Kxe7 19. Qe2+ $18) 13... Bf5 (13... Bxf3 14. gxf3
$16) 14. Nh4 {
Still working to get the Bishop off of the diagonal leading to e6.} 14... O-O-O
$2 {Black misses the point.} 15. Nxf5 (15. Nxf5 Nxf5 16. Be6 $18) 1-0

