1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 Nc6 $2 4. fxe5 Nxe5 5. d4 Nc6 6. e5 Ng8 7. Nf3 {
White has a very pleasant advantage here.} 7... d5 8. Bg5 (8. Bb5 {
also looks good here.}) 8... Be7 9. Qd2 Be6 10. Bb5 {In a few moves we will
see why this is such an important move for White to get in.} 10... Bxg5 (10...
a6 11. Bxc6+ bxc6 12. Bxe7 $1 Nxe7 13. Na4 $1 $16) 11. Nxg5 Nge7 12. Nxe6 fxe6
13. O-O {Now Black cannot castle kingside.} 13... Ng6 14. Bxc6+ $1 bxc6 15. Na4
$1 {Excellent strategic play. White has created an outpost for the Knight at
c5 and now hurries to occupy it.} 15... Qe7 16. Qc3 $1 {
This gains time, as we will see in a moment.} 16... Qd7 17. Nc5 $1 {
Now the Knight arrives on c5 with an attack on Black's Queen.} 17... Qc8 18.
Qh3 $1 {The pressure grows against e6.} 18... Ke7 19. Rf2 {
Simple chess: White will double up on the f-file} 19... Nf8 20. Raf1 Ke8 21.
Qf3 $1 {Now there is no defense against the invasion of the Queen.} 21... Rb8
22. Qxf8+ $1 (22. Qxf8+ Rxf8 23. Rxf8+ Ke7 24. R1f7#) 1-0

