1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 Nc6 $2 {This move looks like it develops a piece,
but actually Black ends up losing a great deal of time.} 4. fxe5 Nxe5 5. d4 {
Of course. White builds a big center "free of charge" while Black's Knights
are tripping over themselves to get out of the way.} 5... Ng6 6. e5 {
Time for the other Knight to go!} 6... Qe7 7. Qe2 Ng8 8. Nf3 d6 $4 {
A very common error.} 9. Nd5 $1 Qd8 (9... Qe6 {
is of course unplayable because of} 10. Nxc7+ {winning the Queen.}) 10. Nxc7+
$1 {A nice twist at the finish.} (10. Nxc7+ Qxc7 11. exd6+ {wins the Queen.})
1-0

