1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 Nc6 4. fxe5 Nxe4 $2 {A misguided combination.} 5.
Nxe4 $1 Qh4+ 6. Ng3 $1 Nxe5 7. Nf3 {
Trading down right away -- a perfectly acceptable way to play.} (7. d4 {
is also very strong.}) 7... Nxf3+ 8. Qxf3 d6 9. Bb5+ Ke7 {
Black must have felt miserable here!} (9... c6 {allows the standard trick} 10.
Bxc6+ $1 bxc6 11. Qxc6+ $18) 10. O-O f6 11. Re1+ Be6 {Cutting short the agony.}
12. Nf5+ $1 1-0

