1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 Nc6 4. fxe5 Nxe5 5. d4 Nc6 6. e5 Ng8 7. Nf3 Bb4 8.
Bc4 $1 {The right square.} (8. Bd3 $2 {allows} 8... Nxd4 {when} 9. Nxd4 $2 Qh4+
$17 {actually favors Black.}) 8... Nge7 9. Ng5 $1 O-O $2 {
A paradigm case of "castling into it."} 10. Qh5 $1 {A fork.} 10... h6 11. Nxf7
$1 Rxf7 12. Bxf7+ $1 Kf8 (12... Kh8 13. Bxh6 $1 gxh6 14. Qxh6#) (12... Kh7 13.
O-O $1 {Since Black has h6 defended twice, White must not try anything too
fancy too fast.} (13. Bxh6 gxh6 14. O-O {does actually win, but it is
preferable from a practical point of view to avoid sacrificing the piece until
there is a concrete follow-up.}) 13... Nxd4 (13... Ng8 14. Bxg8+ Kxg8 (14...
Qxg8 15. Bxh6 gxh6 16. Rf7+ Kh8 17. Qxh6+ Qh7 18. Qxh7#) 15. Bxh6 gxh6 16. Qg6+
Kh8 17. Rf7 Qg8 18. Qxh6+ Qh7 19. Qxh7#) 14. Bxh6 gxh6 15. Bg6+ Nxg6 16. Rf7+
Kg8 17. Qxg6+ Kh8 18. Qh7#) 13. O-O $1 d6 14. Be6+ $1 1-0

