1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 d5 4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Nf3 Be7 6. d3 Nxc3 7. bxc3 O-O 8.
Be2 f6 9. O-O fxe5 10. Nxe5 Bf6 11. Bf4 Nd7 {Here the Knight cuts off Black's
Queen from control of d5, a point that becomes important in a few moves.} 12.
d4 c5 (12... Nxe5 {was forced.}) 13. Bf3 $1 {The pressure on d5 secures the
Knight on e5 against capture -- a point Black does not understand.} 13... Nxe5
14. dxe5 $1 Be7 15. Qxd5+ Kh8 16. Bg3 (16. Qxd8 Bxd8 17. Be3 Be7 18. Bd5 $18 {
Black is all tied up and White's extra pawn should win in the end.}) 16... h6
17. Qxd8 Rxd8 18. Rab1 {
A nice exploitation of the pressure against b7. Now Black blunders.} 18... Rb8
19. e6 $1 Bxe6 20. Bxb8 {The rest of the game needs no comment.} 20... Rxb8 21.
Rfe1 Bxa2 22. Ra1 Bf6 23. Rxa2 Bxc3 24. Re7 c4 25. Kf1 a5 26. Bxb7 Bb4 27. Rc7
c3 28. Rc8+ Rxc8 29. Bxc8 g5 30. Ke2 Kg7 31. Kd3 Kf6 32. Ra1 Ke5 33. Re1+ Kd6
34. Bg4 Kc5 35. Re5+ Kb6 36. Kc4 1-0

