1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 (2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. d3 Nf6 5. Bg5 (5. a3 $5 d6 6. Na4 $14
)) 2... Bc5 3. d3 d6 4. Nc3 Nc6 {We have now transposed into a position that a
Vienna player is more likely to reach by 2.Nc3 Nc6 3.Bc4 Bc5 4.d3 d6.} 5. Na4
Bb6 (5... Qf6 6. Nxc5 dxc5 7. Be3 b6 8. Qd2 Nge7 9. Ne2 Be6 10. Bb5 Qg6 11. O-O
$14 {intending 12.f4 gives White a very comfortable advantage. Note that White
does not play c3, which would give Black a target on the d-file.}) 6. Nxb6 axb6
7. f4 Nf6 8. Nf3 Bg4 9. c3 d5 10. exd5 Nxd5 11. h3 Bxf3 12. Qxf3 Nxf4 13. Bxf4
exf4 14. O-O O-O 15. Qxf4 Qd7 16. d4 Rae8 17. Rf3 Re7 18. Raf1 Nd8 19. Rg3 g6
20. Qh6 Qc6 21. Bb3 Rfe8 22. Rf4 Re4 23. Bxf7+ Nxf7 24. Rxf7 Kxf7 25. Qxh7+ Kf8
26. Rf3+ 1-0

