1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 d5 4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Nf3 Be7 6. d3 Nxc3 7. bxc3 c5 8.
d4 Nc6 9. Bd3 Bg4 10. O-O cxd4 11. cxd4 Nxd4 {
Black thinks that White has blundered.} (11... Qb6 12. c3 Bxf3 13. gxf3 $1 (13.
Rxf3 $5 Nxe5 14. Re3 Nxd3 15. Ba3 $1 O-O 16. Bxe7 Nb2 17. Qh5 Rfe8 18. Rf1 Qg6
19. Qxd5 $18) 13... Nxe5 $4 {
This was the point of ...Qb6, but now Black gets a nasty shock:} 14. Rb1 $1 $18
) 12. Nxd4 $3 {A stunning surprise!} 12... Bxd1 13. Bb5+ $1 Kf8 14. Ne6+ $1 {
The point: this fork picks up Black's Queen, and Black remains a piece behind
because he sacrificed a Knight for a pawn going into this.} 14... Kg8 15. Nxd8
Bh5 16. Nxb7 Rc8 17. Nd6 Rxc2 18. Be8 Be2 19. Rf2 Bd3 20. Bxf7+ Kf8 21. Bg6+ ({
It would be even simpler to play} 21. Rxc2 Bxc2 22. Bxd5 $18) 21... Rxf2 22.
Bxd3 Bh4 23. Be3 Rb2 24. Rf1+ Ke7 25. Nf5+ {Oops.} 1-0

