1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 d5 4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Qf3 Nc6 $1 {This is one of
Black's best ideas against Qf3. It is based on a sneaky tactical idea.} 6. Bb5
$1 {White must know this pin -- it is the only good move.} (6. Nxe4 $4 Nd4 $1
7. Qd3 dxe4 8. Qxe4 Bf5 $19) 6... Bc5 $2 {
Black forgets about the fact that 5.Qf3 threatened to win a pawn.} 7. Nxe4 dxe4
8. Qxe4 O-O 9. Bxc6 $16 b6 $4 {Clearly a mouse slip. Black resigns} 1-0

